 Ngqamakhwe - Ngqamakhwe police are appealing for community assistance in identifying the decomposed body of an unknown man. "It is alleged that a man, who was looking after his stock found a decomposed body of a man on Saturday, at about 08h15, at Sokapase Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Capt Jackson Manatha. "The deceased has not yet been identified. "Anyone who is looking for his male relative can contact Ngqamakhwe Police at 047 487 0017." An inquest docket has been opened for further investigation. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 